Amber Fly Synopsis:

This is what I like to call a newbie quest tutor.  It is not designed
to be difficult at all, in fact, just the opposite.  It was made
for players of level 4 or less that have no clue when
it comes to questing -- not the slightest idea what exactly a
quest is or why anyone would bother to do one.  I was this
type of newbie and learned how to quest the hard way, by doing
them -- both by myself and with others.  This learning process was
painfully slow, so I felt it would be a good thing to design what
I have here in order to simplify the process.

Note: Newbies are not told explicitly what to do in each situation.
At the beginning they are led by the hand, given quite obvious hints
about what to do, but as the quest progresses, the hints tend more
towards the vague side.  To help out, at various stages, they are
referred to a primer which tells them about some aspect of questing,
which just happens to be the one which is relevant to their current
situation.  I tried to be as complete as possible with the primer
docs without being utterly boring.

Starting out, newbies will enter a building where they will acquire
the primer.  This primer directs them down a hall into a den where
they find Ezekiel Milquetoast, the sage.  Comforting him, or
hugging him, as is blatantly hinted at in his description will
reveal the situation: goblins have stolen his little trinket, an
amber fly.  He then directs the player to the courtyard.

In the courtyard, the players will find a hut which houses a blacksmith.
He will ask the player to fill the bucket therein with water so
that he might cool what he is working on.  Doing this is trivial,
as there is a lake nearby, and gains the player a rope with a
grappling hook attached.

From there, the player can climb the willow tree in the orchard
whose branches droop over the courtyard wall, follow the path around
the front of a dark goblin cave to a hole in the ground, and
climb down into a cavern.  After bumping into the wall a few
times, the player will eventually find his way into the
central chamber wherein is found the goblin chieftain and
his assistant the witch doctor.  The latter has the fly in question,
but attacking him is impossible as the chieftain jumps in the way.
Now the chieftain is kind of tough for newbies so the primer has
been equipped with a special function so that it can
burst into a flash of bright light wounding the chieftain and making
him easier to kill; this is to simulate guild powers for the newbie
who will have none.  After the chieftain dies, the witch doctor
flees, leaving the fly behind for the player to take.

Once the fly is returned to Ezekiel, he rewards the player with
a protective aura (AC 20), and the quest is complete with the
newbie a wiser player.

I have placed all the docs for the primer in /open/wizards/lingo/nq_docs
for perusal by all the builders, imps, and supers.  If anyone
feels something important has been omitted or misrepresented,
Please let me know so that I may make the appropriate changes.

